         <p class="- topic/p ">The static bypass consists of the following main parts:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Thyristors (Q401)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Static bypass controller (A401)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Fan with fan monitoring (E401)</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The static bypass provides the following functions:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Built-in PSU supplied from bypass mains input</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Dual speed fan supply for the static bypass fans (the fan speed
is controlled from the interface board via an input contact)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Galvanically isolated thyristor drivers for the static bypass </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Snubber RC networks for the static bypass thyristors</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Output voltage measurement. If the UPS main controller or the
communication interface becomes inoperable, the board monitors the
system output phase-neutral voltage and independently enables the
static bypass if the output is lost</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Communication interface to the UPS controller</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Two signal outputs to indicate the state of the controller</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
